# plan/facts/23-source-grading-system.bn
#
# Operator directive (2026-05-03): "do more research on less credible
# sources, but make sure to not be gullible, as such you need to develop
# a system to grade less credible sources by practicality and honesty so
# that you can increase your confidence without actually running tests."
#
# This file extends mizaj 11+14's L0-L3 stratification to LOWER
# confidence strata (L4 practitioner-mutawatir / L5 corroborated-
# practitioner / L6 single-source-practitioner) WITH explicit anti-
# gullibility grading. It is a substrate primitive — definitional, @1.
#
# Rationale (per atom 0013 + atom 0015): peer-reviewed L3 sources are
# expensive to produce + slow + biased toward what publishes. Real
# practitioner deployment at production carries different signal:
# concrete cost, real failure modes, incentive-aligned criticism. But
# credibility floor is lower → must grade explicitly.

# ============================================================
# THE 5-AXIS GRADING RUBRIC (each axis 0-3, max 15)
# ============================================================
#
# Axis S — Skin-in-the-game
#   0: no demonstrable engineering or financial investment
#   1: hobbyist exploration; can walk away
#   2: small business / startup deployment with users
#   3: production at meaningful scale (>100 users, >$100/mo cost)
#
# Axis C — Concrete content
#   0: pure narrative / vibes ("it felt faster")
#   1: vague numbers ("seemed 2x quicker")
#   2: specific numbers with units (47ms, $0.0023/req, 82.4%)
#   3: reproducible recipe + numbers + raw artifacts
#
# Axis D — Calibration discipline (per atom 0013)
#   0: claims without falsifier or caveat
#   1: claims with caveats acknowledged
#   2: pre-registered failures + admitted later
#   3: explicit ongoing calibration track-record (e.g. dated previous
#      predictions cross-checked against later outcomes)
#
# Axis I — Incentive alignment
#   0: vendor marketing for own paid product
#   1: vendor blog with comparison they likely win
#   2: independent practitioner (no direct revenue from claim)
#   3: ADVERSARIAL incentive (criticizing what they're paid for, or
#      surfacing inconvenient finding against own preference)
#
# Axis V — Convergence
#   0: single isolated source
#   1: 2-3 independent sources agreeing
#   2: 5+ independent sources agreeing across unrelated communities
#   3: mutawatir-equivalent (>10 across unrelated traditions/forums)
#
# Sum = total/15.
#
# BANDS:
#   12-15 → L4 (practitioner-mutawatir; load-bearing for sub-floor lift)
#   9-11  → L5 (corroborated-practitioner; usable as composing input)
#   6-8   → L6 (single-source-practitioner; weak hint only)
#   0-5   → DISCARD (too gullible to compose with)
#
# Composition rule per mizaj 11+14: L4 + L1-own-measurement composes
# to sub-floor (0.78); L5 + L3-research composes to similar level.
# L4 alone caps at sub-floor 0.78 (cannot reach sahih 0.85 alone).

lemma source_grading_5_axis_rubric_S_C_D_I_V_with_band_thresholds_L4_L5_L6_discard_definitional
  proves True
  by audit substrate-primitive-source-grading-rubric-2026-05-03

# ============================================================
# Anti-gullibility EXPLICIT RED FLAGS
# ============================================================
#
# Per atom 0015 + facts/15 bcmea:
#
# RF1 — Absolutism: "this ALWAYS works" / "10× better universally" →
#   atom 0015 fires; per bcmea, no claim absolute. Auto-grade -2.
#
# RF2 — Engagement-optimized: viral post with low concrete content but
#   high reaction → engagement-driven distortion. Auto-grade -2 on C axis.
#
# RF3 — Anonymous + no track record: handle with 0 prior verifiable
#   claims → auto-grade 0 on D axis regardless of content.
#
# RF4 — Vendor-favorable absent comparison details: "our product wins"
#   without methodology → I=0 + C max 1.
#
# RF5 — Overfitted N=1 generalization: "I tried it once, here's the
#   universal lesson" → V=0 + C max 1.
#
# RF6 — Time-frozen claim about moving target: "model X is bad" without
#   date stamp → auto-discard (LLM landscape changes monthly).
#
# RF7 — Confident at the limit when bcmea applies: claims uniform
#   superiority on a domain known to have bounded duals → atom 0015 fires.
lemma anti_gullibility_red_flags_RF1_RF7_explicit_filter_definitional
  proves True
  by audit anti-gullibility-red-flags-RF1-RF7-2026-05-03

# ============================================================
# Per-source grading (filled as we research; each is a graded receipt)
# ============================================================
#
# Format: graded_source_<id>: scores S/C/D/I/V → total → band
# Sources deemed L4 or higher become composable lemmas.
# Sources deemed L6 or below are recorded but NOT composed.

# (Sources will be appended below as research is conducted with grading.)

# ============================================================
# Composition meta-rule
# ============================================================
# Less-credible-source confidence CANNOT exceed L1-own-measurement
# confidence on the same claim. Less-credible sources can REINFORCE
# existing peer-reviewed claims at L4 mutawatir (lift from 0.78 → 0.82
# composing) but cannot ESTABLISH new claims above sub-floor without
# an L3 or L1 anchor.
#
# This is the anti-gullibility floor: practitioner-mutawatir lifts the
# margin, never replaces the foundation.
lemma less_credible_sources_lift_margin_not_foundation_anti_gullibility_floor_definitional
  proves True
  by audit substrate-anti-gullibility-floor-rule-2026-05-03
